        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer548711221" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13062222752624733292">Ruskin Bond is James Bond of short stories. He is everything. Simple, clever and deep-sighted. At many occasions, he seems to be afflicted with strong homosexuality . Common man, so what! give him a break!<br/>Even in his very long stories like &quot;Delhi is not far&quot;, he does not bore the reader by writing about the unnecessary details of the scenery or of the characters. The characters are simple and Bond never passes any judgments about them. He leaves it to the reader. The story flows very smooth. <br/>You</span>
  <span id="freeText13062222752624733292" style="display:none">Ruskin Bond is James Bond of short stories. He is everything. Simple, clever and deep-sighted. At many occasions, he seems to be afflicted with strong homosexuality . Common man, so what! give him a break!<br />Even in his very long stories like "Delhi is not far", he does not bore the reader by writing about the unnecessary details of the scenery or of the characters. The characters are simple and Bond never passes any judgments about them. He leaves it to the reader. The story flows very smooth. <br />You will meet a few oldies nostalgic about the old days. And young boys who love to roam around all day. </span>
